Core Conflict
GEAR's entire purpose for four millennia has been to observe unchanging data. The party represents the first truly chaotic, unpredictable variable he has encountered since his entire race vanished. He wants to understand why mortals behave "illogically," but in doing so, he may discover that he himself is more than just a machineΓÇöthat buried deep in his suppressed neural matrix is the last fragment of a living Dwemer mind.
High Concept
The Prototype Mind. A Dwemer construct running a suppressed "snapshot" of a researcher's brain, now an immortal scholar seeking to understand the illogical world of mortals while slowly uncovering the ghost in his own machine.

