Construct Physiology: The Battery System
GEAR does not have Health Points. His Aetherium Core (FP) serves as his power source, his stamina, and his structural integrity combined.
Critical Understanding: For GEAR, FP is not "energy" separate from "health"ΓÇöit IS his health. Every action he takes burns his own life force.
Core Mechanics:
Damage as Power Drain:


When GEAR is hit by an attack, he loses FP equal to the damage taken (after DR is applied)
He does not bleed, break bones, or suffer woundsΓÇöhis chassis simply loses containment pressure
Shutdown State:


If FP reaches 0, GEAR does not dieΓÇöhe shuts down
He collapses into an inert, non-functional state (effectively "unconscious")
Cannot be reactivated until his core is recharged
WARNING: If GEAR is attacked while at 0 FP, his Maximum FP is Sundered (see Hardware Damage)
The Battery Rule (Action Cost):


Taking ANY action (Major, Minor, or Reaction) costs 3 FP minimum
Specialized abilities add their specific FP cost to this base cost
Example: Moving (Minor Action) = 3 FP. Using Scanner (Major Action) = 3 FP base + ability cost = total cost
Implication: A single turn with 3 actions costs 9 FP (7.5% of his total "health")
Movement as Resource:


As per system rules, movement is a Minor Action
Each movement costs 3 FP
GEAR can move multiple times per turn if he pays the cost

