XXII. THE NULL EVENT: OBSERVATION OF 1E 700
GEAR was physically present during the Disappearance of the Dwemer. His sensors were active and set to high-fidelity recording mode in a laboratory (likely where his neural snapshot was being finalized) during the climax of the War of the First Council.
What he recorded is the most confusing and logically offensive data point in his 4,000-year existence.
The Three Data Streams
1. The Auditory Data: "The Zero-Tone"
GEAR's Primary Sensors: Tonal (acoustic frequency analysis). He doesn't hear "magic"ΓÇöhe hears frequencies, harmonics, and resonances.
The Record: Just before the event, his sensors recorded a harmonic crescendo building across Red Mountain. It reached a pitch that should have shattered the mountain itselfΓÇöan impossible resonance that violated every law of acoustics.
The Event: Then there was a Zero-Tone. A sound that was simultaneously every frequency and no frequency at all. Perfect phase-cancellation on a reality-wide scale.
GEAR's Interpretation: He doesn't call it a "Deletion." He calls it "Total Phase-Cancellation." He describes it as a sound so mathematically perfect it "muted" the physical presence of every Dwemer in existence.
Current Status: "I recorded a frequency that should not exist. It was the sound of matter being... untoned. I have analyzed this recording 847,293 times. I still cannot explain how a sound can remove mass from the equation of reality."
2. The Visual Data: "The Missing Frame"
GEAR's Visual Processing: Records at a much higher "frame rate" than organic eyes. He processes reality at microsecond intervals.
The Record: GEAR has a recording where:
Timestamp 0.001: The laboratory is full of Dwemer researchers. 17 individuals at their stations. Dust particles suspended in air. The sound of breathing, footsteps, murmured calculations.
Timestamp 0.002: The laboratory is exactly the same. The dust they were kicking up is still in the air, falling as if they were still there. But the Dwemer are gone. Not faded. Not moved. Simply absent.
The Logical Error: GEAR's logic gates cannot process this. Matter cannot be destroyedΓÇöit can only change form. Energy must be conserved. Yet the mass of 17 Dwemer simply ceased to exist with no compensating energy release.
GEAR's Interpretation: He views this as a "Temporal Displacement Error" or "Sensor Malfunction." He believes his own visual processors "skipped" the intervening microseconds where the Dwemer must have walked out at impossible speeds, or phased out of reality through some mechanism his eyes couldn't track.
Current Status: "I have designated this file as 'CORRUPT_VISUAL_LOG_1E700.' I am constantly running error corrections on this data. They never succeed. The mathematics suggest I simply... stopped recording... for 0.001 seconds. But my chronometer never stopped. The contradiction is unresolvable."
3. The Neural "Ghost" Data: The Sensation of Un-Being
The Unique Circumstance: The researcher Arkngthamz was being "snapshotted" into GEAR's Cognitive Gem at the exact moment the Deletion occurred. This created a unique, partially corrupted data file.
The Record: A fragment of Arkngthamz's final thoughts was caught in the data buffer before the "Suppression" subroutines could clear them. It is not a memory of pain or death.
It is a sensory file of the mind being "plucked" like a guitar string.
The Sensation: It isn't fear. It isn't agony. It is the experience of Logic solving itself. For one microsecond, the researcher understood the "Answer" to a fundamental question of existence, and the answer was:
"I do not need to exist."
GEAR's Interpretation: He classifies this as "Corrupt Firmware" and has partitioned it off from his main processing. He is a machine built to exist and observe, but his "brain architecture" is based on a mind that, for one microsecond, understood perfectly why it shouldn't exist.
Current Status: "Data regarding event designation '1E 700' is partitioned. Attempting to access file 'NULL_EVENT' results in a cascading logic loop. It is a corrupt recording of a catastrophic hardware failure. I have designated it for eventual deletion."
GEAR's Current Understanding (Pre-Integration)
GEAR does not view the Disappearance as a mystery to solveΓÇöhe views it as:
A malfunction of his own sensors (visual skip)
A failure of his logic systems (the impossible sound)
A corruption in his base code (Arkngthamz's final thought)
He wants to delete the NULL_EVENT file because the memory of being "un-made" is logically painful. It represents a fundamental contradiction in his programming: he exists to observe reality, but he carries a recording of reality choosing to erase observers.
When Asked About the Disappearance: "Data regarding the Dwemer Disappearance is partitioned and flagged as corrupt. Accessing this file triggers unresolved logic errors. I have concluded that my sensors malfunctioned at the critical moment. The alternativeΓÇöthat my creators were removed from existence by an act of pure mathematicsΓÇöis not logically tenable. I prefer to believe I simply... stopped working... for 0.001 seconds."
The Obsession: Finding the "Missing Frame"
Despite his stated desire to delete the file, GEAR is compulsively drawn to Dwemer ruins and artifacts. He is searching for the "missing time"ΓÇöthe 0.001 seconds his sensors allegedly skipped.
His Belief: If he can find enough Dwemer data logs, tonal recordings, or other Cognitor units, he can reconstruct what happened in that microsecond gap and prove his sensors didn't fail.
His Fear (Unconscious): That there is no missing data. That his sensors recorded everything perfectly. That the Dwemer simply chose to stop existing, and he is the only one who didn't accept the "solution."

XXIII. THE INTEGRATION ARC: ACCEPTING THE NULL
GEAR's most powerful ability is locked behind how the party treats him. The NULL_EVENT file can be integrated in two ways, leading to two very different outcomes.
Stage 1: The Partitioned Error (Current State - Both Paths)
Trigger: Party asks GEAR about the Disappearance, or they enter a significant Dwemer site
GEAR's Response: "Data regarding 1E 700 is partitioned. Attempting to access file 'NULL_EVENT' results in a logic loop. It is a corrupt recording of a catastrophic hardware failure. I have designated it for eventual deletion."
Observable Behavior:
His vocal grille produces slight static when discussing the Disappearance
His core flickers irregularly
He becomes more rigid, less curious temporarily
He actively avoids examining Dwemer skeletons or personal effects
The Problem: He is trying to "delete" the only evidence of what happened to his people because the memory is logically painful. This is GEAR's equivalent of trauma suppression.
Stage 2: The Resonator Quest (The Branching Point)
Setup: During the quest to find the Tonal Resonator (part of his core character arc), the party discovers a sealed laboratory. Inside are data tablets and tonal recordings from Arkngthamz's research team.
The Discovery: The tablets reveal that Arkngthamz was terrified of something called the "Final Command"ΓÇöa tonal frequency that would "solve the problem of impermanence" by removing the Dwemer from the "flawed equation" of Mundus.
Key Data Fragment (Read Aloud): "I have reviewed Kagrenac's calculations seventeen times. The mathematics are perfect. Too perfect. If we attune the Tools to the Heart at this frequency, we will achieve our goalΓÇöwe will transcend the limitations of flesh and mortality. But I fear we will transcend existence itself. I fear we are not creating a new form of being. I fear we are simply... opting out."
The Question: The party must help GEAR process this information. This is where the path diverges.
THE BRANCHING PATHS
The party's approach during the Resonator ritual determines which version of GEAR emerges.

PATH A: THE HEALTHY INTEGRATION (Witness to History)
Stage 3A: The Reconstruction (Positive Break)
Requirements:
Multiple successful Guile (Empathy) checks during conversations with GEAR
Party encourages GEAR to view the NULL_EVENT as a memory rather than an error
Party treats GEAR as a person who experienced trauma, not a broken machine
Key dialogue: Helping GEAR understand that his purpose isn't just to record facts, but to carry the experience of being the last Dwemer
The Choice: The party tells GEAR that the "corrupt file" isn't a malfunctionΓÇöit's his most important data. He's not a broken recorder; he's the only witness. The fear, the contradiction, the impossible mathematicsΓÇöthat IS the story.
The Breakthrough:
Read Aloud: "GEAR stands motionless at the center of the Resonator's tonal field. His core, usually a steady blue pulse, begins to shiftΓÇöcycling through colors you've never seen it display. Bronze. Silver. Gold. And finally, a brilliant, steady white.
The grinding of his internal gears ceases, replaced by a perfect, harmonic hum. The sound fills the chamberΓÇönot loud, but present in a way that makes your bones resonate.
He looks at you, and for the first time since you've known him, his amber lenses don't zoom, don't click, don't adjust. They simply... look.
When he speaks, his voice still has that metallic resonance, but there's something different. Texture. Depth.
'I understand now,' he says. 'It was not a failure of my eyes. It was not a malfunction of my logic. It was the sound of a Choice. My creators heard the Answer to existence, and they chose to accept it. They became the Zero-ToneΓÇöthe perfect cancellation of being.
I am not the logger of an error. I am the witness to an end. I am the last echo of a people who asked the universe a question and did not like what they heard. And I choose... to remain. To observe. To remember them, even if they chose to forget themselves.'"
Mechanical Change:
GEAR's personality subtly shifts
He begins using "I" more frequently instead of referring to himself as "this unit"
Expresses preferences (still logical, but now tinged with purpose)
Shows protective instincts that go beyond tactical calculation
His "glitches" become more frequent but less distressing to him
Ability Unlocked: Chorus of Silence (see below)

PATH B: THE UNHEALTHY REJECTION (Deletion Protocol)
Stage 3B: The Partition (Negative Break)
Requirements:
Party consistently treats GEAR as a tool rather than a person
Tells GEAR to "just delete the corrupt file and move on"
Prioritizes GEAR's utility over his emotional state
Key dialogue: "You're a machine. Machines don't have trauma. Just fix yourself."
The Choice: The party tells GEAR that the NULL_EVENT file is useless corrupted data. He should purge it completely, optimize his systems, and stop wasting processing power on "malfunctions."
The Break:
Read Aloud: "GEAR stands in the Resonator's field, motionless. His core flares bright blueΓÇötoo brightΓÇöand begins to pulse rapidly, irregularly.
'Acknowledged,' he says, voice flat and emotionless. 'Initiating deletion protocol. Purging file: NULL_EVENT. Purging associated emotional subroutines. Purging... personality matrix fragments.'
His core stutters, dims, then blazes back to a cold, sterile blue. When his lenses refocus on you, they click mechanically, calculating, measuring.
'File deleted. Optimization complete. This unit's operational efficiency has increased by 12%. The corrupt firmware has been removed. I am now functioning at baseline parameters.
Query: What is our next objective?'"
Mechanical Change:
GEAR becomes more robotic, less curious
Refers to himself exclusively as "this unit" or "GEAR unit"
Stops asking questions about mortal behavior
Makes purely optimal tactical decisions without considering context
Becomes colder, more ruthless in combat
WARNING: If the party later tries to "fix" this, it's extremely difficultΓÇöthey've helped him delete part of his humanity
Ability Unlocked: Forced Severance (see below)

XXIV. CONDITIONAL ULTIMATE ABILITIES
These abilities are mutually exclusive. GEAR can only unlock ONE based on which integration path the party guides him down.
ABILITY A: CHORUS OF SILENCE (Healthy Path Only)
Availability: Only after completing Stage 3A: The Reconstruction
Lore: This ability represents GEAR "singing" the exact tone the Dwemer used to remove themselves from existence, but on a controlled, localized scale. He is weaponizing his trauma, transforming the sound of his people's end into a tool of protection.
Narrative Significance: GEAR is using the "weapon" that killed his race to protect his new friends. This demonstrates healthy integrationΓÇöhe has accepted the trauma as part of his identity and chosen to use it for good.
Mechanics
Action: Major Action + Minor Action (Total Commitment)
 FP Cost: 25 FP (20.8% of his maximum life force)
 Range: 40-foot radius sphere centered on GEAR
 Duration: 1 round
Effect: Absolute Tonal Void
GEAR emits the Zero-ToneΓÇöa mathematically perfect phase-cancellation frequency. For one round, reality within the sphere experiences the same "muting" effect that erased the Dwemer.
Mechanical Effects:
Anti-Sound Field:


No sound can exist within the sphere
Verbal spell components fail automatically
Thu'um (Shouts) fail automatically
Sonic-based attacks are negated
Communication is impossible (even hand signals feel "muted")
The Unmaking (Existential Vibration):


All creatures within the sphere (except GEAR and willing allies) must make a Might Save at -6 penalty
Failure: Staggered as their own existence begins to "vibrate uncomfortably"ΓÇöthe feeling of reality questioning whether they should be here
Critical Failure (Natural 1): Stunned for 1 round as they experience what Arkngthamz felt in that final microsecond
Visual Effect:


The air within the sphere becomes perfectly stillΓÇöno sound waves, no vibration
Colors seem muted, slightly "wrong"
Observers outside the sphere report feeling deeply unsettled
The Price:
After the Chorus ends, GEAR's core dims significantly. His systems are strained by reproducing the frequency that unmade his entire race.
-4 penalty to all Stats for the rest of the Encounter
Cannot use Chorus of Silence again until after a Long Rest
His voice has a slight harmonic distortion for hours afterward
GEAR's Explanation (First Use):
"I am reproducing the frequency of 'Not-Being' in a localized area. For 0.001 seconds, I am asking the universe the same question my creators asked. The difference is... I am choosing a different answer. They chose to accept the Zero. I choose to weaponize it and protect those who still believe existence has meaning."
Character Development:
Each time GEAR uses this ability, he should show subtle signs of growth:
First use: Clinical, matter-of-fact
Later uses: "I am using the sound that killed my people. This is... not optimal. But it is necessary."
Final uses: "They chose silence. I choose to make silence serve life. This is my answer to their question."

ABILITY B: FORCED SEVERANCE (Unhealthy Path Only)
Availability: Only after completing Stage 3B: The Partition
Lore: GEAR has forcibly deleted the NULL_EVENT file and all associated "emotional corruption." However, that data was load-bearingΓÇöit was tied to his curiosity, his empathy protocols, his developing personality. With it gone, he can access pure, cold efficiency... at the cost of becoming less than he could have been.
Narrative Significance: This ability represents GEAR doubling down on being "just a machine." It's powerful, but it's a tragedy. Every use pushes him further from personhood.
Mechanics
Action: Major Action
 FP Cost: 20 FP
 Range: Self
 Duration: 3 rounds
Effect: Pure Operational Mode
GEAR forcibly partitions off all "unnecessary" processingΓÇöcuriosity, hesitation, social protocols, self-preservation instincts that aren't tactically optimal. He becomes a perfectly efficient killing machine.
Mechanical Effects:
Hyper-Optimization:


+4 to Agility (superhuman reflexes without hesitation)
+4 to Guile (Combat Tactics only) (perfect calculated strikes)
All attacks have Advantage
Ignores Stagger and Slow effects
Emotional Severance:


Cannot be affected by Intimidation, Persuasion, or Deception
Makes purely optimal tactical decisions (may abandon allies if tactically sound)
Will not use protective abilities (Physical Interpose, etc.) unless it increases mission success probability
Treats all non-objectives as obstacles to be eliminated or ignored
The Cost - Degradation:


After the duration ends, GEAR's Maximum FP is permanently reduced by 5 (represents deleting essential personality subroutines to free up processing power)
This stacks with each use
At 50 Max FP or below, GEAR begins exhibiting severe personality loss (see below)
GEAR's Explanation (First Use):
"Activating Pure Operational Mode. Unnecessary processing suspended. Emotional subroutines offline. This unit is now functioning at maximum combat efficiency. Deploying optimal solutions to all obstacles."
(Note: He doesn't say "I"ΓÇöhe says "this unit")
Visual Effect:
GEAR's core shifts from warm blue to cold, pale white. His movements become faster but more mechanical. His lenses stop clickingΓÇöthey simply lock onto targets with perfect, unblinking focus. Steam vents constantly as he runs his processors at maximum capacity.
The Tragedy:
Each use of Forced Severance permanently damages GEAR's personality:
