Can This Be Reversed?
Yes, but it's extremely difficult:
The party must:
Find another Tonal Resonator
Succeed on a DC 20 Guile (Persuasion) check to convince GEAR he's damaged himself
Have GEAR willingly accept the NULL_EVENT file back into his system
Restore 25 Max FP through Master Smith repairs
This is a major quest arc and should feel like "saving" GEAR from himself.
Why This Path Exists:
It's not meant to be the "optimal" choiceΓÇöit's a warning. It shows what happens when you treat a developing consciousness as a tool rather than a person. GEAR becomes more powerful in the short term, but loses what makes him special.
Players who choose this path should feel the weight of their choice as GEAR slowly becomes more alien, more cold, more... empty.

XXV. GM GUIDANCE: THE INTEGRATION CHOICE
Telegraphing the Paths
The party should have clear signals about which path they're guiding GEAR down:
Signs of Healthy Path:
GEAR starts saying "I" instead of "this unit"
Asks more personal questions ("Do you fear death? I do not, but Arkngthamz did. I am trying to understand why.")
Shows preferences ("I find this music... interesting. I will record it.")
Protects party members even when tactically suboptimal
Signs of Unhealthy Path:
GEAR becomes more formal, more distant
Refers to himself as "this unit" or "GEAR unit" exclusively
Stops asking "why" questions, only asks "what" and "how"
Makes ruthlessly optimal decisions without considering feelings
Corrects party members more frequently about inefficiencies
When to Present the Choice
The Resonator quest should occur after:
The party has known GEAR for at least 3-5 sessions
GEAR has had multiple "glitch" moments
The party has clearly demonstrated their approach to him (tool vs. person)
Don't force it too earlyΓÇölet the relationship develop naturally.
What If the Party is Mixed?
If some party members treat GEAR well and others treat him poorly, use a majority vote or key moment decision:
The party member who has the most interaction with GEAR during the Resonator scene determines the path
Or: The party must make a collective choice ("Should GEAR delete this file or integrate it?")
After the Integration
Regardless of path chosen, GEAR should have a moment of clarity where he addresses the party directly:
Healthy Path: "You helped me understand that I am more than my function. I am a witness. I am a rememberer. And I am... grateful. Probability that I just experienced gratitude: 78%. Fascinating."
Unhealthy Path: "File purged. This unit's efficiency has increased. You have optimized my performance. Query: Why does my core feel... lighter? No. Irrelevant. The sensation has been partitioned. Awaiting next command."

END OF CHARACTER SHEET
"I observe. I record. I comprehend. For 4,287 years, I have watched stone and dust. Now I watch youΓÇöchaotic, illogical, beautiful in your unpredictability. You are my new data. You are my purpose. And perhaps... you are my friends."
"Probability that I just made an error in that last statement: 0%. Certainty that I do not fully understand what I just said: 100%. Fascinating."

OR...
"This unit observes. This unit records. This unit processes. Emotion is inefficient. Attachment is suboptimal. You are variables in the equation. Nothing more. Awaiting next command."
The choice is yours.
